adjectives.description: unwedgeable (comparative more unwedgeable, superlative most unwedgeable)

entries.meaning: That cannot be split, as with a wedge.
examples: Strong, tough as the oak-root, and as gnarled and unwedgeable; no fibre of him running straight with the other: a block for Destiny to beat on, for the world to gaze at, with ineffectual wonder!
